package AssertPkg;

public class ToBeTestedEg {
    public int add2No(int x, int y){
        return x + y;
    }
    public static int sq(int x){
        return x * x;
    }

}




package AssertPkg;

public class AssertEg {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ToBeTestedEg t1=new ToBeTestedEg();
        assert (t1.add2No(2,3) == 5) : "Incorrect fn: add2No()";
        System.out.println("Post assertion....code continues..");
    }
}




By default, assertions are disabled. We need to run the code as given. The syntax for enabling assertion statement in Java source code is:
java –ea Test
Or
java –enableassertions Test
Disabling Assertions
The syntax for disabling assertions in java are:
java –da Test
Or
java –disableassertions Test
Here, Test is the file name.




